OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777370785
OL,3,CStarmer faces vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row as ex-officials due to
OL,5,Cgive evidence
OL,7,FThe prime minister also faces
OL,8,Fpotentially damaging testimony from
OL,9,FMorgan McSweeney, his former chief of
OL,10,Fstaff, and former top civil servant in
OL,11,Fthe Foreign Office, Sir Phillip
OL,12,FBarton. They are set to give evidence
OL,13,Fto the Foreign Affairs Select
OL,14,FCommittee on Tuesday morning.
OL,16,FBoth men were summoned by the chair of
OL,17,Fthe committee, Dame Emily Thornberry,
OL,18,Fto give evidence about Peter
OL,19,FMandelson's appointment as ambassador
OL,20,Fin Washington.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777370785
OL,3,CStarmer faces vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row as ex-officials due to
OL,5,Cgive evidence
OL,7,FMandelson was sacked from his position
OL,8,Flast year after revelations came to
OL,9,Flight about his close relationship
OL,10,Fwith convicted paedophile Jeffrey
OL,11,FEpstein.
OL,13,FHis sacking and the release of
OL,14,Fdocuments about his appointment have
OL,15,Fcreated further headaches for the
OL,16,Fprime minister, which now largely
OL,17,Fcentre around the fact that UK
OL,18,FSecurity Vetting recommended Mandelson
OL,19,Fnot be given security clearance, only
OL,20,Fto be overruled by the Foreign Office.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777370785
OL,3,CStarmer faces vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row as ex-officials due to
OL,5,Cgive evidence
OL,7,FMcSweeney, widely regarded as a
OL,8,Fprotege of Lord Mandelson, resigned in
OL,9,FFebruary, saying at the time he took
OL,10,F"full responsibility" for advising
OL,11,FStarmer to appoint Mandelson as US
OL,12,Fambassador.
OL,14,FHis resignation statement read: "In
OL,15,Fpublic life, responsibility must be
OL,16,Fowned when it matters most, not just
OL,17,Fwhen it is most convenient. In the
OL,18,Fcircumstances, the only honourable
OL,19,Fcourse is to step aside.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777370785
OL,3,CStarmer faces vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row as ex-officials due to
OL,5,Cgive evidence
OL,7,F"This has not been an easy decision.
OL,8,FMuch has been written and said about
OL,9,Fme over the years, but my motivations
OL,10,Fhave always been simple: I have worked
OL,11,Fevery day to elect and support a
OL,12,Fgovernment that puts the lives of
OL,13,Fordinary people first and leads us to
OL,14,Fa better future for our great country.
OL,16,F"Secondly, while I did not oversee the
OL,17,Fdue diligence and vetting process, I
OL,18,Fbelieve that process must now be
OL,19,Ffundamentally overhauled. This cannot
OL,20,Fsimply be a gesture but a safeguard
OL,21,Ffor the future."
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
